Example Activity data for São Paulo (20 agents)

Source: R/sao_paulo_activity_df_20.R
sao_paulo_activity_df_20.Rd

Each row of this table contains a single trip of 20 different agents in the São Paulo city.

sao_paulo_activity_df_20

Format

A data frame with columns:

ZONA

Household zone.

MUNI_DOM

Household municipality.

CO_DOM_X

Household coordinate X.

CO_DOM_Y

Household coordinate Y.

ID_DOM

Household identifier.

F_DOM

Identify first household record.

FE_DOM

Household expansion factor.

DOM

Household number.

CD_ENTRE

Interview code.

DATA

Date of interview.

TIPO_DOM

Type of household.

AGUA

Do you have piped water?.

RUA_PAVI

Is the street paved?.

NO_MORAD

Household size.

TOT_FAM

Total families in the household.

ID_FAM

Family identifier.

F_FAM

Identify first family record.

FE_FAM

Famiy expansion factor.

FAMILIA

Family number

NO_MORAF

Family size.

CONDMORA

Housing condition.

QT_BANHO

Bathrooms.

QT_EMPRE

Domestic workers.

QT_AUTO

Automobiles.

QT_MICRO

Microcomputers.

QT_LAVALOU

Dishwashers.

QT_GEL1

One door refrigerator.

QT_GEL2

Two door refrigerator.

QT_FREEZ

Frezers.

QT_MLAVA

Washing machines.

QT_DVD

DVDs.

QT_MICROON

Microwave oven.

QT_MOTO

Motorcycles.

QT_SECAROU

Clothes dryer.

QT_BICICLE

Bikes.

NAO_DCL_IT

Comfort item declaration code.

CRITERIOBR

Critério de Classificação Econômica Brasil.

PONTO_BR

Critério Brasil points.

ANO_AUTO1

Year of manufacture of Auto 1.

ANO_AUTO2

Year of manufacture of Auto 2.

ANO_AUTO3

Year of manufacture of Auto 3.

RENDA_FA

Person number.

SIT_FAM

Age.

Education.

Labor market status.

CO_REN_I

Individual income.

ZONA_ESC

School zone.

MUNIESC

CO_ESC_X

School coordinate X.

CO_ESC_Y
